Followup_Security_IncognitoSafe: Please indicate how much you agree or disagree with each statement. -Incognito mode / private browsing mode in browsers prevents websites from collecting information about you.
Followup_Security_IPIdentify: Please indicate how much you agree or disagree with each statement. -Internet Protocol (IP) addresses can always uniquely identify your computer.
Followup_Security_SecureHTTPS: Please indicate how much you agree or disagree with each statement. -When a website uses "https" in its web address, it secures communication between a person's computing device and the website itself.
Followup_Security_VPNVisible: Please indicate how much you agree or disagree with each statement. -When using Virtual Private Network (VPN), network traffic is easily visible to others.
Followup_Security_WIFINotVisible: Please indicate how much you agree or disagree with each statement. -When using Wi-Fi, your network traffic is never visible to other people using the same network.
Followup_Security_WIFIBroadcast: Please indicate how much you agree or disagree with each statement. -During Wi-Fi use, a computing device broadcasts data in order to access online information.
Followup_Security_Paypal: Please indicate how much you agree or disagree with each statement. -PayPal is a type of credit card used for online shopping.
Followup_TwoWks_Intro: The questions that follow ask about your / computing and online behaviors during the PAST TWO WEEKS...
Followup_Device_Lock: Indicate how often you did the following things during the past two weeks.-I had my computer screen automatically lock if I didn’t use it for a prolonged period of time.
Followup_Device_Password: Indicate how often you did the following things during the past two weeks.-I used a password/passcode to unlock my laptop or tablet.
Followup_Device_ManualLock: Indicate how often you did the following things during the past two weeks.-I manually locked my computer screen when I stepped away from it.
Followup_Device_PIN: Indicate how often you did the following things during the past two weeks.-I used a PIN or passcode to unlock my mobile phone.
Followup_Proactive_NoLinkVerify: Indicate how often you did the / following things during the past two weeks.-When someone sent me a link, I opened it without first verifying where it went.
Followup_Proactive_LookFeel: Indicate how often you did the / following things during the past two weeks.-I knew what website I was visiting based on its look and feel, rather than by looking at the URL bar.
Followup_Proactive_NoSubmitVerify: Indicate how often you did the / following things during the past two weeks.-I submitted information to websites without first verifying that it would be sent securely.
Followup_Proactive_Mouseover: Indicate how often you did the / following things during the past two weeks.-When browsing websites, I mouseovered links to see where they went, before clicking them.
Followup_Proactive_AssumeFix: Indicate how often you did the / following things during the past two weeks.-If I discovered a security problem, I continued what I was doing because I assumed someone else would fix it.
Followup_Updating_Prompt: Indicate how often you did the following things during the past two weeks.-When I was prompted about a software update, I installed it right away.
Followup_Updating_Programs: Indicate how often you did the following things during the past two weeks.-I tried to make sure that the programs I used were up-to-date.
Followup_Updating_Antivirus: Indicate how often you did the following things during the past two weeks.-I verified that my anti-virus software had been regularly updating itself.

Followup_WIFI_Autoconnect: While using Wi-Fi, / indicate how often you did the following things during the / past two weeks. -I allowed my devices to automatically connect to the nearest Wi-Fi access point.
Followup_WIFI_LeftBrowserOpen: While using Wi-Fi, / indicate how often you did the following things during the / past two weeks. -I left my browser window open when I was done using it.
Followup_WIFI_LoggedOut: While using Wi-Fi, / indicate how often you did the following things during the / past two weeks. -I logged out of my online user accounts (e.g., online shopping, e-mail, social network sites, etc.) when I finished using them.

Followup_WIFI_NonSensitive: While using Wi-Fi, / indicate how often you did the following things during the / past two weeks. -I did non-sensitive online activities over open or public Wi-Fi.
Followup_WIFI_HTTPS: While using Wi-Fi, / indicate how often you did the following things during the / past two weeks. -I paid attention to whether websites used “https” in their URL.
